cs.IT, cs.CC, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.NI 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper proposes a new class of lattices constructed from polar codes to achieve the capacity of the AWGN channel. This falls under the domain of information theory. 
2. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper discusses the complexity of encoding and decoding the proposed polar lattices, which could fall under the domain of computational complexity. 
3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - Although the paper does not explicitly discuss social or information networks, the proposed polar lattices could potentially be used in network communication systems. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses the multilevel approach used to construct the polar lattices, which could fall under the domain of data structures and algorithms. 
5. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - Similar to cs.SI, the proposed polar lattices could potentially be used in networking systems, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture.
